techmeme.title: Baidu unveils smart glasses powered by its Ernie LLM that aim to "become a private assistant" by tracking calories, playing music, and more, launching in 2025 (Eleanor Olcott/Financial Times)
SoftBank says Vision Fund co-CEO Rajeev Misra will step down from his leadership roles; during his 10-year tenure, he led investments in WeWork, Wag, and others (Manish Singh/TechCrunch)
SoftBank reports Q2 net income of ~$7.7B and a Vision Fund gain of ~$2.42B, driven by strong Indian IPOs and valuation gains in startups like Coupang and Didi (Bloomberg)
Rival search engines Ecosia and Qwant launch European Search Perspective, a joint venture to develop an index of the web to reduce reliance on Google and Bing (Paresh Dave/Wired)
Amazon's Annapurna Labs plans to unveil "Trainium 2" AI chips next month, in an effort that can rival Nvidia; Trainium 2 is being tested by Anthropic and others (Financial Times)
